{"id": "EUVD-2024-50472", "enisaUuid": "313eaef8-d1cd-3df4-adb1-937ec234b75f", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/mediatek: Fix potential NULL dereference in mtk_crtc_destroy()\n\nIn mtk_crtc_create(), if the call to mbox_request_channel() fails then we\nset the \"mtk_crtc->cmdq_client.chan\" pointer to NULL.  In that situation,\nwe do not call cmdq_pkt_create().\n\nDuring the cleanup, we need to check if the \"mtk_crtc->cmdq_client.chan\"\nis NULL first before calling cmdq_pkt_destroy().  Calling\ncmdq_pkt_destroy() is unnecessary if we didn't call cmdq_pkt_create() and\nit will result in a NULL pointer dereference.", "datePublished": "2024-11-19T17:19:39", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:17", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c60583a87cb4a85b69d1f448f0be5eb6ec62cbb2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4018651ba5c409034149f297d3dd3328b91561fd"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53056"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1ed193b4-3f37-3ab2-96be-8eafff4df87d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7627122fd1c06800a1fe624e9fb3c269796115e8 <4018651ba5c409034149f297d3dd3328b91561fd"}, {"id": "1eed9f5d-113c-3b5e-ab80-718bcc7714dd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "42150524-50e2-3f4f-b0f5-ba3c06818050", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2c4396693698e876e559768d3d3a150c672ec384"}, {"id": "81642766-1152-35a9-b84b-89de532f0d11", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.7"}, {"id": "b58bdf98-2bdd-3b5f-b26c-a937ab2cf029", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "c9aaf52e-4f0e-3ec2-951b-0f41c5ad2f3d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "d8ae1559-f012-3605-a770-97f3342a325d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7627122fd1c06